</tbody>
</table>
<p>This table provides a clear overview of the customer journey stages, the actions taken by users, the touchpoints they encounter, and the emotional goals they aim to achieve at each stage. This summary can help organizations understand the customer experience better and identify areas where improvements can be made.</p></div>
                <div class="thought reaction">
                    <span class="thought-label">Reaction</span>
                    <span class="category-tag">Explicit Affirmation</span>
                    The table is well-organized and serves as a perfect executive-level summary of the journey.
                </div>
