<td><strong>Brick Size</strong></td>
<td><strong>0.30 – 0.75 SPY points</strong> (~$0.30–$0.75)</td>
<td>Start with <strong>0.50</strong> (adjust based on volatility)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Timeframe</strong></td>
<td><strong>1-minute or 2-minute Renko bricks</strong></td>
<td>Avoid 5-minute bricks (too slow for day trading)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Confirmation</strong></td>
<td><strong>Wait for a closed brick</strong> before entering</td>
<td>Prevents false breakouts</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Color Scheme</strong></td>
<td><strong>Green = Bullish, Red = Bearish</strong></td>
<td>Standard Renko convention</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>🔹 <strong>Why 0.30–0.75?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>SPY moves in <strong>~0.20–0.50 point increments</strong> intraday.</li>
<li><strong>0.50</strong> is a good starting point (adjust based on <strong>ATR(14)</strong>).</li>
<li>If SPY is <strong>volatile (ATR &gt; 1.0)</strong>, use <strong>0.75 bricks</strong>.</li>
<li>If SPY is <strong>choppy (ATR &lt; 0.5)</strong>, use <strong>0.30 bricks</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><strong>🔹 Entry Rules (High-Probability Setups)</strong></h3>
<h4><strong>📈 Long (Buy) Entry Conditions</strong></h4>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Bullish Renko Signal</strong>
   - A <strong>green brick closes above the previous green brick’s high</strong>.
   - <em>Example</em>: If the last brick closed at <strong>$500.20</strong>, wait for a new green brick to close <strong>above $500.20</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Volume Confirmation (Optional but Recommended)</strong>
   - <strong>Volume spike</strong> (if trading SPY directly) or <strong>unusual options activity</strong> (if trading SPY calls/puts).
   - Use <strong>Volume Profile</strong> (e.g., above 20-day average).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Trend Filter (Avoid Counter-Trend Trades)</strong>
   - <strong>20-period EMA &gt; 50-period EMA</strong> (bullish trend).
   - <strong>Slope of 20 EMA is upward</strong> (no bearish divergence).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Key Level Breakout (Optional but High-Conviction)</strong>
   - Trade <strong>only if SPY is above the opening range high</strong> (e.g., first 30 min).
   - Or, <strong>breakout above a recent swing high</strong> (e.g., yesterday’s close).</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>✅ <strong>Best Time for Longs:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>9:30–11:30 AM ET</strong> (first 2 hours = strongest trends).</li>
<li><strong>1:30–3:30 PM ET</strong> (post-lunch trends often resume).</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>📉 Short (Sell) Entry Conditions</strong></h4>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Bearish Renko Signal</strong>
   - A <strong>red brick closes below the previous red brick’s low</strong>.
   - <em>Example</em>: If the last brick closed at <strong>$499.80</strong>, wait for a new red brick to close <strong>below $499.80</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Volume Confirmation (Optional)</strong>
   - <strong>Volume spike</strong> or <strong>unusual put options activity</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Trend Filter</strong>
   - <strong>20 EMA &lt; 50 EMA</strong> (bearish trend).
   - <strong>Slope of 20 EMA is downward</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Key Level Breakdown (Optional)</strong>
   - Trade <strong>only if SPY is below the opening range low</strong>.
   - Or, <strong>breakdown below a recent swing low</strong>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>✅ <strong>Best Time for Shorts:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>9:30–11:30 AM ET</strong> (if SPY gaps down).</li>
<li><strong>1:30–3:30 PM ET</strong> (if trend resumes downward).</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><strong>🔹 Exit Rules (Profit &amp; Risk Management)</strong></h3>
<h4><strong>1. Trailing Stop (Best for SPY)</strong></h4>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Exit Method</th>
<th>Long Trade</th>
<th>Short Trade</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>ATR-Based</strong></td>
<td>Exit when price closes <strong>below 1.5x ATR(14)</strong> from entry</td>
<td>Exit when price closes <strong>above 1.5x ATR(14)</strong> from entry</td>
<td><em>Default method</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Fixed Stop</strong></td>
<td><strong>$0.50–$1.00 stop loss</strong> (adjust based on volatility)</td>
<td>Same as long</td>
<td>Simple but less adaptive</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Opposite Brick Signal</strong></td>
<td>Exit when a <strong>red brick forms</strong></td>
<td>Exit when a <strong>green brick forms</strong></td>
<td>Aggressive, but works well in trends</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Fibonacci Extension</strong></td>
<td>Take profit at <strong>1.618 or 2.618</strong> of brick size</td>
<td>Same as long</td>
<td>Works in strong trends</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4><strong>2. Profit Targets (Risk-Reward Ratio)</strong></h4>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Strategy</th>
<th>Entry</th>
<th>Stop Loss</th>
<th>Take Profit (Partial)</th>
<th>Take Profit (Full)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>1:1.5 R:R</strong></td>
<td>$500.00</td>
<td>$499.70 (30c)</td>
<td>$500.15 (15c)</td>
<td>Trail the rest to 1.5x</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>1:2 R:R</strong></td>
<td>$500.00</td>
<td>$499.50 (50c)</td>
<td>$500.25 (25c)</td>
<td>Trail to 2x</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Scalp + Run</strong></td>
<td>$500.00</td>
<td>$499.80 (20c)</td>
<td>50% at 30c profit</td>
<td>Let the rest run</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>💡 <strong>Best Practice:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Exit 50% at 1:1 R:R</strong> (locks in profit).</li>
<li><strong>Let the rest run</strong> with a trailing stop.</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><strong>🔹 Filters to Increase Win Rate</strong></h3>
<h4><strong>1. Pre-Market Bias (9:00–9:30 AM ET)</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>If <strong>SPY opens above yesterday’s close +0.5%</strong>, favor <strong>longs</strong>.</li>
<li>If <strong>SPY opens below yesterday’s close -0.5%</strong>, favor <strong>shorts</strong>.</li>
<li>If <strong>gap is too small (&lt;0.3%)</strong>, avoid trading (choppy market).</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>2. Volume Filter (Intraday)</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Volume &gt; 20-day average</strong> (confirms participation).</li>
<li><strong>Unusual options activity</strong> (check SPY options flow on platforms like <strong>Barchart, FlowAlgo</strong>).</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>3. VIX Filter (Avoid Choppy Markets)</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>VIX &gt; 25</strong> → Market is volatile, avoid trading.</li>
<li><strong>VIX &lt; 15</strong> → Market is calm, Renko works best.</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>4. Opening Range Breakout (ORB) Filter</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>First 30 minutes (9:30–10:00 AM ET)</strong> define the <strong>opening range (OR)</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Trade only if SPY breaks out of OR</strong> in the direction of the Renko signal.</li>
<li><em>Example</em>: If OR is <strong>$499.50–$500.50</strong>, trade <strong>only if SPY &gt; $500.50 (long) or &lt; $499.50 (short)</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>5. Moving Average Filter</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>20 EMA &gt; 50 EMA</strong> → Only take longs.</li>
<li><strong>20 EMA &lt; 50 EMA</strong> → Only take shorts.</li>
<li><em>Avoid counter-trend trades.</em></li>
</ul>
<hr>
