<th>Action</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>1. Setup</strong></td>
<td>Brick size = 0.50, 2-min Renko, 20 EMA &gt; 50 EMA.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>2. Entry</strong></td>
<td>Green brick closes <strong>above $500.20</strong> at 10:15 AM.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>3. Stop Loss</strong></td>
<td>Below <strong>$499.90</strong> ($0.30 risk).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>4. Take Profit (50%)</strong></td>
<td>Exit half at <strong>$500.35</strong> ($0.15 profit).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>5. Trail Rest</strong></td>
<td>Move stop to breakeven at $500.20, then trail with <strong>1.5× ATR</strong>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>6. Exit</strong></td>
<td>Price closes below <strong>$500.10</strong> (trailing stop hit).</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
