<p>That said, <strong>Renko <em>can</em> work for scalping</strong>—<strong>if you optimize it correctly</strong>. Below is a <strong>realistic, high-probability Renko scalping strategy</strong> for <strong>SPY, ES (E-mini S&amp;P), or forex majors</strong> (EUR/USD, GBP/USD).</p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>🎯 Renko Scalping Strategy (1–5 Minute Bricks)</strong></h2>
<h3><strong>1. Brick Size: The #1 Scalping Killer</strong></h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Market</strong></th>
<th><strong>Brick Size (Renko)</strong></th>
<th><strong>Why?</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>SPY</strong></td>
<td><strong>0.10–0.20 points</strong> (~$0.10–$0.20)</td>
<td>SPY moves in tiny increments intraday.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>ES (E-mini S&amp;P)</strong></td>
<td><strong>1–2 points</strong></td>
<td>ES ticks in 0.25 increments, so 1–2 points = 4–8 ticks.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>EUR/USD (Forex)</strong></td>
<td><strong>0.5–1 pip</strong></td>
<td>Forex moves fast; small bricks filter noise.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>GBP/USD</strong></td>
<td><strong>1–2 pips</strong></td>
<td>More volatile than EUR/USD.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>🔹 <strong>Key Rule</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Brick size = 1–2 × average tick/point move in the last 14 periods (ATR).</strong></li>
<li><strong>Too small?</strong> → Noise kills you.</li>
<li><strong>Too large?</strong> → Miss fast scalps.</li>
</ul>
