<li><strong>GBP/USD with 1–2 pip brick size</strong> (2-min bricks).</li>
</ol>
<h3><strong>💀 Worst Renko Scalping Setups</strong></h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Scalping in ranges (VIX &gt; 20, ATR &lt; 0.20 SPY points).</strong></li>
<li><strong>Using 5-min Renko bricks</strong> (too slow for scalping).</li>
<li><strong>Ignoring volume filters</strong> (fake breakouts).</li>
<li><strong>Trading without a stop loss</strong> (one bad trade = disaster).</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3><strong>📌 Renko Scalping Checklist (Before Every Trade)</strong></h3>
<p>✅ <strong>Brick size = 1–2 × average tick move (ATR × 0.5)?</strong>
✅ <strong>Volume &gt; 20-day average?</strong>
✅ <strong>ATR(14) &gt; 0.20 SPY points (or equivalent)?</strong>
✅ <strong>VIX &lt; 20?</strong>
✅ <strong>20 EMA &gt; 50 EMA (for longs) or 20 EMA &lt; 50 EMA (for shorts)?</strong>
✅ <strong>Stop loss set (not wider than 1.5× ATR)?</strong>
✅ <strong>Profit target planned (1:1.5 R:R)?</strong></p>
<hr>
<h3><strong>🎯 Pro Tips to Improve Renko Scalping</strong></h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Use a trailing stop (1.5× ATR) instead of opposite bricks</strong> (better in trends).</li>
<li><strong>Trade only the first 2 hours (9:30–11:30 AM ET)</strong>—most liquidity.</li>
<li><strong>Avoid scalping around news (8:30 AM, 2 PM ET)</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Combine with Volume Profile</strong>—trade only at key levels.</li>
<li><strong>Start with 1 contract/share</strong>—scale up only after 50+ consistent trades.</li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3><strong>📊 Realistic Expectations (What to Aim For)</strong></h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Account Size</strong></th>
<th><strong>Risk per Trade</strong></th>
<th><strong>Daily P/L Goal</strong></th>
<th><strong>Monthly P/L Goal</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>$5,000</strong></td>
<td>$50 (1%)</td>
<td>+$20–$30</td>
<td>+$400–$600</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>$10,000</strong></td>
<td>$100 (1%)</td>
<td>+$30–$50</td>
<td>+$600–$1,000</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>$25,000</strong></td>
<td>$250 (1%)</td>
<td>+$50–$80</td>
<td>+$1,000–$1,600</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>$50,000</strong></td>
<td>$500 (1%)</td>
<td>+$80–$120</td>
<td>+$1,600–$2,400</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr>
<h3><strong>🔥 Bottom Line: Renko for Scalping?</strong></h3>
<p>✅ <strong>Works well in trending markets</strong> (SPY, ES, forex majors).
✅ <strong>Reduces noise</strong> compared to traditional scalping.
✅ <strong>High win rate (55–65%)</strong> if optimized correctly.</p>
<p>❌ <strong>Fails in choppy/ranging markets</strong> (VIX &gt; 20).
❌ <strong>Requires strict discipline</strong> (no overtrading).
❌ <strong>Lag can be a problem</strong> in fast markets.</p>
<h3><strong>🚀 Final Recommendation</strong></h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Start with SPY or ES</strong> (most liquid for scalping).</li>
<li><strong>Use 1–2 min Renko bricks, 0.10–0.20 SPY points</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Paper trade for 2–4 weeks</strong> before going live.</li>
<li><strong>Stick to the plan</strong>—don’t revenge trade.</li>
<li><strong>Scale up slowly</strong> (only increase size after 3+ months of consistency).</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Would you like a Renko scalping script for TradingView or NinjaTrader?</strong> 🚀</p></div>
