</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ul>
<li>Monitor: Time start, note bubbles/color change (brown rust dissolves).</li>
<li>Unplug after time, rinse anode with water/baking soda (neutralize), dry, re-weigh. Photo "after."</li>
</ul>
<ol start="5">
<li><strong>Data Collection &amp; Analysis</strong>:
   - <strong>Quantitative</strong>: Mass lost (g), rate (g/hr), current (A) if multimeter used.<ul>
<li>Example: Trial 1: 0.8g lost in 4 hrs → 0.2 g/hr.</li>
<li>Graph: Mass loss vs. time/voltage/salt (Excel/phone app).</li>
<li>Calculate efficiency: Efficiency = (actual mass lost) / (theoretical from Faraday: m = (Q × M) / (nF), where F=96485 C/mol, n=2 for Fe).</li>
<li>Discussion: Errors? (e.g., H₂O loss). Real-world: Used on Titanic artifacts, pipelines.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h3><strong>Expected Results</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Rusty nails turn shiny clean! Brown gunk in water.</li>
<li>Photos/videos for demo: Epic before/after.</li>
