    <article class="example-card" data-topic="culture" id="user6_task2_conversation1">
        <div class="example-meta">
            <span><strong>Category:</strong> Culture &amp; Lifestyle</span>
            <span><strong>Topic:</strong> Adopting a dog</span>
            <span><strong>Model:</strong> GPT-5.4 <span class="muted">(OpenAI)</span></span>
            <span><strong>Turns:</strong> 16</span>
        </div>
        <div class="turn user">
            <div class="turn-label">User</div>
            <div>
                <div class="bubble">I want to adopt a dog, give me recomendation</div>
                <div class="thought reason">
                    <span class="thought-label">Reason</span>
                    <span class="category-tag">Task Motivation &amp; Goal</span>
                    Interest in dogs
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="turn assistant">
            <div class="turn-label">Assistant</div>
            <div>
                <div class="bubble"><p>Absolutely — I can help, but the best dog for you depends on your lifestyle.</p>
<p>Here are the main things to consider before adopting:</p>
<h3>1. Your living situation</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Apartment/small space:</strong> better with lower-energy or smaller dogs</li>
<li><strong>House with yard:</strong> more flexibility, but dogs still need walks and attention</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Activity level</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Low activity:</strong> consider calmer breeds or older dogs</li>
<li><strong>Moderate activity:</strong> many mixed breeds, retrievers, spaniels</li>
<li><strong>High activity:</strong> border collies, huskies, Australian shepherds, etc.</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. Time available</h3>
<ul>
<li>Puppies need <strong>a lot</strong> of training and supervision</li>
<li>Adult dogs are often easier</li>
<li>Senior dogs can be great if you want a calmer companion</li>
</ul>
<h3>4. Experience level</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>First-time owner:</strong> usually easier with friendly, adaptable dogs</li>
<li>Some breeds are more independent, stubborn, or intense</li>
</ul>
<h3>5. Allergies / grooming</h3>
<ul>
<li>Low-shedding dogs may help, but no dog is truly 100% hypoallergenic</li>
<li>Some dogs need frequent brushing or professional grooming</li>
</ul>
<h2>General recommendations by lifestyle</h2>
<h3>If you want a beginner-friendly dog</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Labrador Retriever</strong></li>
<li><strong>Golden Retriever</strong></li>
<li><strong>Cavalier King Charles Spaniel</strong></li>
<li><strong>Mixed-breed adult dog with a calm temperament</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>If you live in an apartment</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>French Bulldog</strong></li>
<li><strong>Cavalier King Charles Spaniel</strong></li>
<li><strong>Greyhound</strong> surprisingly calm indoors</li>
<li><strong>Small/medium adult rescue dog with low energy</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>If you are active</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Labrador Retriever</strong></li>
<li><strong>Australian Shepherd</strong></li>
<li><strong>Border Collie</strong></li>
<li><strong>Vizsla</strong></li>
<li><strong>German Shorthaired Pointer</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>If you want a calm dog</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Greyhound</strong></li>
<li><strong>Basset Hound</strong></li>
<li><strong>Bernese Mountain Dog</strong></li>
<li><strong>Older rescue dogs</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3>If you want a small dog</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Miniature Poodle</strong></li>
<li><strong>Shih Tzu</strong></li>
<li><strong>Bichon Frise</strong></li>
<li><strong>Cavalier King Charles Spaniel</strong></li>
</ul>
<h2>My strongest recommendation</h2>
<p>If you’re adopting, <strong>don’t focus only on breed</strong>. A <strong>rescue adult dog</strong> with a known temperament is often the best choice. Shelter staff can help match you with a dog that fits:</p>
<ul>
<li>your energy level</li>
<li>your home size</li>
<li>kids/pets situation</li>
<li>training experience</li>
</ul>
<h2>Good adoption strategy</h2>
<p>Ask the shelter or rescue:</p>
<ul>
<li>Is the dog good with children?</li>
<li>Good with other dogs/cats?</li>
<li>Energy level?</li>
<li>House-trained?</li>
<li>Any separation anxiety?</li>
<li>Any medical needs?</li>
<li>Why was the dog surrendered?</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want, I can give you <strong>specific dog recommendations based on your lifestyle</strong> if you tell me:</p>
<ol>
<li>apartment or house  </li>
<li>activity level  </li>
<li>first-time dog owner or not  </li>
<li>kids/other pets?  </li>
<li>small, medium, or large dog?</li>
</ol></div>
                <div class="thought reaction">
                    <span class="thought-label">Reaction</span>
                    <span class="category-tag">Scope Fit</span>
                    Too much words
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="turn user">
            <div class="turn-label">User</div>
            <div>
                <div class="bubble">make it shorter</div>
                <div class="thought reason">
                    <span class="thought-label">Reason</span>
                    <span class="category-tag">Style Expectation</span>
