<li>Often try to <strong>herd</strong> kids, pets, or people</li>
<li>Shed quite a bit</li>
</ul>
<h3>My take</h3>
<p>If you want a dog that will <strong>run, play, and train a lot</strong>, an Australian Shepherd can be excellent.</p>
<p>If you want a more relaxed big dog, a <strong>Labrador</strong> or <strong>Golden Retriever</strong> is usually easier.</p>
<p>So:  </p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Active owner?</strong> Australian Shepherd = good choice  </li>
<li><strong>Want easier/friendlier for most homes?</strong> Labrador/Golden = better</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want, I can compare <strong>Australian Shepherd vs Labrador</strong> for you.</p></div>
