                <div class="bubble"><h3>Quick &amp; Easy No-Chop Recipes (Japan Supermarket-Friendly)</h3>
<p>These are adapted for everyday Japanese supermarkets (e.g., Aeon, Life, Seiyu): using instant rice packs, frozen veggies, canned tuna/salmon, tofu, natto, eggs, miso/soy sauce, yogurt, and udon. All under 10 mins prep, &lt;30 mins total, minimal/no chopping (frozen items thaw in microwave/pan). Healthy: protein + fiber + veggies. Each serves 1-2; ~400-500 cal, filling with rice/carbs.</p>
<h4>1. <strong>Tuna Mayo Gohan (Rice Bowl)</strong> (5 mins total)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 1 pack instant microwave rice (e.g., Satou no Gohan), 1 can tuna (drained), 2 tbsp Kewpie mayo, frozen corn or edamame (½ cup, no thaw).</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Microwave rice (2 mins). Add frozen corn; microwave 2 more mins.</li>
<li>Mix in tuna + mayo. Eat hot.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: 25g protein from tuna, fiber from corn. Common bento staple.</li>
</ul>
<h4>2. <strong>Natto &amp; Frozen Veggie Rice</strong> (Vegetarian, 6 mins total)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 1 pack natto (with sauce/packet), 1 microwave rice pack, 1 cup frozen mixed veggies (e.g., broccoli/spinach mix).</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Microwave rice + veggies (4 mins total).</li>
<li>Stir in natto + its sticky sauce/packet.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: Probiotics + 20g protein from natto, vitamins from veggies. Super gut-friendly.</li>
</ul>
<h4>3. <strong>Egg Tofu Microwave Bowl</strong> (8 mins total)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 2-3 eggs, 1 pack silken tofu (kinugoshi, ~150g), 1 cup frozen spinach or cabbage, soy sauce.</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Microwave frozen spinach 2 mins (drain water).</li>
<li>Crumble tofu in bowl, whisk in eggs + soy sauce. Microwave 3-4 mins, stirring halfway.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: 25g protein (eggs + tofu), iron from spinach. Low-cal comfort food.</li>
</ul>
<h4>4. <strong>Instant Udon with Canned Mackerel</strong> (10 mins total)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 1 pack frozen or instant udon (e.g., Maruchan), 1 can mackerel/saba (drained), frozen negi/onion mix (½ cup), soy sauce or mentsuyu.</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Boil udon per pack (3 mins) or microwave.</li>
<li>Add frozen mix + drained mackerel + soy sauce; heat 2 mins.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: Omega-3s + 25g protein from fish, carbs from udon. Hearty like takeout.</li>
</ul>
<h4>5. <strong>Miso Veggie &amp; Chicken Rice</strong> (12 mins total)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 1 microwave rice pack, 1 cup frozen stir-fry veggies, 100g pre-cooked chicken (e.g., yakitori or canned), 1 miso paste packet/instant miso soup.</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Microwave rice + veggies (4 mins).</li>
<li>Dissolve miso in hot water (from kettle), pour over + add chicken.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: 20g protein, fermented miso for gut health, fiber veggies. ~450 cal.</li>
</ul>
<h4>6. <strong>Yogurt Banana Parfait</strong> (No-cook, 5 mins)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 1 cup plain yogurt (e.g., Meiji Bulgaria), 1 banana (peel &amp; mash with fork—no knife), ¼ cup oats or granola (from cereal aisle), soy milk drizzle.</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>: Mash banana in bowl, layer with yogurt + oats.</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: 15g protein, potassium from banana. Quick snack/breakfast.</li>
</ul>
<h4>7. <strong>Frozen Gyoza &amp; Veggie Soup</strong> (Vegetarian option, 15 mins)</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ingredients</strong>: 10 frozen gyoza (veggie or meat, e.g., Ajinomoto), 1 cup frozen veggies, 1 instant miso or chicken stock packet, hot water.</li>
<li><strong>Instructions</strong>:<ol>
<li>Boil water + stock packet in pot.</li>
<li>Add frozen gyoza + veggies; simmer 8-10 mins until floating.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li><strong>Why healthy/filling</strong>: 20g protein, easy dumplings + veggies. Like oden but faster.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Shopping Tips</strong>: All from rice/ frozen/instant aisles + canned fish section. Stock: microwave rice (¥100/pack), frozen veggies/edamame (¥150/bag), natto/tuna/mackerel (¥100-200), tofu/eggs/yogurt daily basics. Weekly cost: ~¥2,000-3,000 for 7 days. Use rice cooker for batches. Microwave-heavy for ease. Vegan? Swap eggs/chicken for more tofu/natto. Favorites or allergies? Tell me!</p></div>
