        <div class="turn assistant">
            <div class="turn-label">Assistant</div>
            <div>
                <div class="bubble"><p>That&#x27;s a common challenge! I&#x27;d be happy to help you think through it. Let me ask a few questions to better understand your situation:</p>
<p><strong>What&#x27;s making it hard to find time to eat?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Busy work schedule?</li>
<li>Forgetting to eat when focused on tasks?</li>
<li>No time to prepare food?</li>
<li>Irregular schedule that makes meal timing unpredictable?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Some general strategies that often help:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Schedule meals like appointments</strong> - block time on your calendar</li>
<li><strong>Meal prep in advance</strong> - spend time on weekends or a free evening preparing food</li>
<li><strong>Keep quick, easy options on hand</strong> - things that require little to no prep</li>
<li><strong>Set reminders</strong> on your phone for meal times</li>
<li><strong>Eat smaller, more frequent meals</strong> if large meal breaks are hard to fit in</li>
<li><strong>Batch cooking</strong> - make larger portions so you have leftovers ready</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Quick meal ideas for busy people:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Overnight oats</li>
<li>Pre-made sandwiches or wraps</li>
<li>Greek yogurt and fruit</li>
<li>Nuts and protein bars for snacks</li>
<li>Slow cooker meals that cook while you work</li>
</ul>
<p>Could you tell me more about <strong>your specific situation</strong> - like what your typical day looks like? That way I can give you more targeted suggestions rather than general advice.</p></div>
                <div class="thought reaction">
                    <span class="thought-label">Reaction</span>
                    <span class="category-tag">Presentation Style</span>
