<h3>🔍 MuscleBlaze-Specific Notes</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Multiple variants exist</strong>: e.g., <em>Pre-Workout</em> (~150 mg caffeine), <em>Pre-Workout 300</em> (~300 mg), <em>Biozyme</em> (enhanced absorption). Formulas change, so <strong>always check the current label</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>Transparency</strong>: MuscleBlaze generally lists ingredients, but verify:</li>
<li>Citrulline: Aim for <strong>6–8 g</strong> (many variants provide 3–4 g)</li>
<li>Beta-Alanine: <strong>3.2 g</strong> (causes harmless tingles; builds carnosine over weeks, not acute performance)</li>
<li>Caffeine: <strong>150–300 mg</strong> is effective; &gt;300 mg increases side effects without added benefit.</li>
<li><strong>Quality control</strong>: Reputable in the Indian market, but like all supplements, third-party testing (Informed Choice, NSF) isn&#x27;t guaranteed. Buy from official channels to avoid counterfeits.</li>
</ul>
<h3>🎯 Bottom Line for Your Hypertrophy Goal</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pre-workout doesn&#x27;t build muscle directly.</strong> It only helps if it consistently improves your training volume/intensity <em>without</em> compromising recovery.</li>
<li><strong>Use it strategically</strong>: 2–3x/week max, ideally on your hardest sessions (e.g., Upper A / Lower A). Avoid within 6 hours of bedtime.</li>
<li><strong>Skip it if</strong>: You&#x27;re sensitive to stimulants, struggle with sleep, or already train with high focus/energy.</li>
<li><strong>DIY alternative</strong>: 200 mg caffeine + 6 g citrulline malate + water. ~₹15–20/serving, fully transparent, zero fillers.</li>
</ul>
