                <div class="bubble"><h1>Bidet Installation Guide</h1>
<h2>Types &amp; Installation Complexity</h2>
<p><strong>Bidet Toilet Seats</strong> (easiest)</p>
<ul>
<li>Replace existing toilet seat</li>
<li>Plug into nearby outlet</li>
<li>Connect water supply line</li>
<li>~30 minutes, no plumbing needed</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Bidet Attachments</strong> (moderate)</p>
<ul>
<li>Mount under existing seat</li>
<li>Connect to toilet&#x27;s water supply</li>
<li>~20-30 minutes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Standalone Bidets</strong> (hardest)</p>
<ul>
<li>Requires separate fixture and plumbing</li>
<li>May need professional installation</li>
<li>Involves water and drain lines</li>
</ul>
<h2>Basic Steps (Toilet Seat/Attachment)</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Turn off water</strong> at toilet shutoff valve</li>
<li><strong>Remove old seat</strong> (unscrew bolts)</li>
<li><strong>Mount new bidet</strong> following manufacturer instructions</li>
<li><strong>Connect water supply</strong> using T-valve on toilet&#x27;s fill line</li>
<li><strong>Plug in</strong> (if electronic)</li>
<li><strong>Test</strong> before full use</li>
</ol>
<h2>What You&#x27;ll Need</h2>
<ul>
<li>Adjustable wrench</li>
<li>Screwdrivers</li>
<li>Possibly a T-valve adapter</li>
<li>Teflon tape (for connections)</li>
</ul>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul>
<li>Read your specific model&#x27;s instructions first</li>
<li>Check water pressure compatibility</li>
<li>Ensure outlet access (for electronic models)</li>
<li>Keep shutoff valve accessible</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For standalone bidets</strong>, professional plumbing installation is usually recommended.</p>
<p>Any specific type you&#x27;re considering?</p></div>
