            <div>
                <div class="bubble"><h1>Tushy 3.0 Installation Steps</h1>
<h2>Before You Start</h2>
<ul>
<li>Turn off water at toilet shutoff valve (behind/below toilet)</li>
<li>Gather: adjustable wrench, the Tushy box contents</li>
<li>Read Tushy&#x27;s included instructions alongside these</li>
</ul>
<h2>Installation Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Remove old toilet seat</strong>
   - Unscrew bolts on underside of seat
   - Lift seat and lid off</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Install Tushy mounting plate</strong>
   - Place mounting plate on toilet bowl rim
   - Align holes with bowl&#x27;s bolt holes
   - Insert bolts through plate and tighten (don&#x27;t over-tighten)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Attach bidet seat</strong>
   - Lower Tushy onto mounting plate
   - Secure according to instructions (usually clips or screws)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Connect water supply</strong>
   - Locate fill valve (where water enters tank)
   - Turn off water valve
   - Disconnect hose from fill valve
   - Attach T-valve adapter to fill valve
   - Reconnect tank hose to one side of T-valve
   - Connect Tushy&#x27;s water line to other side
   - Wrap connections with Teflon tape if needed</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Turn water back on</strong>
   - Check for leaks
   - Adjust water pressure dial on Tushy (if applicable)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Test</strong>
   - Use controls to test spray
   - Adjust settings as needed</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2>Tushy-Specific Notes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Tushy 3.0 is non-electric (no outlet needed)</li>
<li>Water pressure adjustment dial on side</li>
<li>Simple controls on arm</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Stuck?</strong> Tushy&#x27;s website has video tutorials that are very helpful.</p></div>
